ord, Mississippi|Oxford]] (36 times), and [[Jackson, Mississippi|Jackson]] (29 times); there have been a few meetings in other locations including [[Tupelo, Mississippi|Tupelo]] 3 times, [[Greenwood, Mississippi|Greenwood]] twice, [[Clarksdale, Mississippi|Clarksdale]] once, and [[Columbus, Mississippi|Columbus]] once.  Through 2019, in total the two squads have met on the gridiron 116 times with Ole Miss holding a 62\u201346\u20136 lead in the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://static.hailstate.com/custompages/pdf/fb/fb_postgame_112218.pdf |title=POST GAME NOTES |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=22 Nov 2018 |website=HAIL STATE |publisher=Mississippi State Athletics |access-date=23 Nov 2018 |quote=\"With tonight\u2019s win, MSU improves to 45-64-6 in the all-time series history.\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://olemisssports.com/news/2018/11/22/football-postgame-notes-vs-mississippi-state.aspx |title=Postgame Notes vs. Mississippi State |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=22 Nov 2018 |website=OLE MISS SPORTS |publisher=University of Mississippi |access-date=23 Nov 2018 |quote=\"Ole Miss holds a 64-45-6 advantage in the series\"}}</ref>\n\n===LSU===\n{{main article|LSU\u2013Mississippi State football rivalry}}\nThe LSU\u2013Mississippi State rivalry is an annual football game between the [[LSU Tigers Football|Louisiana State Tigers]] and Mississippi State University Bulldogs. Both universities are founding members of the Southeastern Conference, as well as the Western Division. This rivalry is LSU's longest rivalry with 108 meetings.\n\nMississippi State's 34\u201329 victory on September 20, 2014 was the Bulldogs' first over LSU since 1999, their first in Baton Rouge since 1991, and just their fourth overall since 1985.\n\nThe 1976 game was won on the field by Mississippi State but later deemed by the NCAA to have been forfeited, therefore lost, by the bulldogs.\n\n===Alabama===\n{{main article|Alabama\u2013Mississippi State football rivalry}}\nThe Alabama\u2013Mississippi State rivalry, sometimes referred to as the 90 Mile Drive or the Battle for Highway 82, is an annual football game between the [[Alabama Crimson Tide Football|University of Alabama Crimson Tide]] and Mississippi State University Bulldogs. Both universities are founding members of the Southeastern Conference, as well as the Western Division. The two campuses are located approximately 90 miles apart, and are the closest SEC schools in terms of distance.\n\nEntering its 97th meeting as of the 2012 football season, Alabama-Mississippi State is one of the SEC's longest-running series, dating back to 1896.\n\n=== All-time record vs. SEC teams ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Mississippi State Bulldogs|Opponent|Won|Lost|Tied|Percentage|Streak|First|Last}}\n|- \n| [[Alabama Crimson Tide football|Alabama]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.winsipedia.com/mississippi-state/vs/alabama|title=Winsipedia - Mississippi State Bulldogs vs. Alabama Crimson Tide football series history|website=Winsipedia}}</ref> || 18 || 82 || 3 || {{winpct|18|82|3}} || Lost 12 || 1896 || 2019\n|- \n| [[Arkansas Razorbacks football|Arkansas]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.winsipedia.com/mississippi-state/vs/arkansas|title=Winsipedia - Mississippi State Bulldogs vs. Arkansas Razorbacks football series history|website=Winsipedia}}</ref> || 13 || 16 || 1 || {{winpct|13|16|1}} || Won 3 || 1916 || 2019\n|- \n| [[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.winsipedia.com/mississippi-state/vs/auburn|title=Winsipedia - Mississippi State Bulldogs vs. Auburn Tigers football series history|website=Winsipedia}}</ref> || 27 || 64 || 3 || {{winpct|27|64|3}} || Lost 1 || 1905 || 2019\n|- \n| [[Florida Gators football|Florida]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.winsipedia.com/mississippi-state/vs/florida|title=Winsipedia - Mississippi State Bulldogs vs. Florida Gators football series history|website=Winsipedia}}</ref> || 19 || 34 || 2 || {{winpct|19|34|2}} || Lost 1 || 1