n|- style=\"background:#{{CollegeSecondaryHex|Michigan Wolverines}}\"\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''' National championships'''\n| colspan=\"2\"| '''11'''\n|}\n\n;Unclaimed national championships\nIn addition to the 11 national championships that Michigan claims, the school has been named national champion by various \"major selectors\" featured in the NCAA record book for five other seasons.<ref name=\"ncaabook\" /> Michigan does not claim national championships for these years.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Michigan Wolverines|Year|Coach|Selector|Record|Bowl}}\n|-\n| [[1925 Michigan Wolverines football team|1925]] || Fielding H. Yost || Sagarin || 7\u20131 ||\n|-\n| [[1926 Michigan Wolverines football team|1926]] || Fielding H. Yost || Sagarin || 7\u20131 || \n|-\n| [[1964 Michigan Wolverines football team|1964]] || [[Bump Elliott]] || Dunkel || 9\u20131 || Won [[1965 Rose Bowl|Rose]]\n|-\n| [[1973 Michigan Wolverines football team|1973]] || [[Bo Schembechler]] || NCF, Poling || 10\u20130\u20131 ||\n|-\n| [[1985 Michigan Wolverines football team|1985]] || Bo Schembechler || [[Matthews Grid Ratings|Matthews]] || 10\u20131\u20131 || Won [[1986 Fiesta Bowl|Fiesta]]\n|}\n\n;Other undefeated seasons\nMichigan was also undefeated in 11 other seasons: [[1879 Michigan Wolverines football team|1879]], [[1880 Michigan Wolverines football team|1880]], [[1884 Michigan Wolverines football team|1884]], [[1885 Michigan Wolverines football team|1885]], [[1886 Michigan Wolverines football team|1886]], [[1887 Michigan Wolverines football team|1887]], [[1898 Michigan Wolverines football team|1898]], [[1910 Michigan Wolverines football team|1910]], [[1922 Michigan Wolverines football team|1922]], [[1930 Michigan Wolverines football team|1930]], [[1992 Michigan Wolverines football team|1992]].\n\n===Conference championships===\nThe following is a list of Michigan's 42 conference championships as of 2019.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Michigan Wolv