 shared.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Miami Hurricanes|Year|Conference|Coach|Overall record|Conf. record}}\n|-\n| [[1991 Miami Hurricanes football team|1991]] || rowspan=\"9\"|[[Big East Conference (1979\u20132013)|Big East]] || rowspan=\"3\" | [[Dennis Erickson]] || 12-0 || 2-0\n|-\n| [[1992 Miami Hurricanes football team|1992]] || 11-1 || 4-0\n|-\n| [[1994 Miami Hurricanes football team|1994]] || 10\u20132 || 7\u20130\n|-\n| [[1995 Miami Hurricanes football team|1995]]\u2020 || rowspan=\"3\" | [[Butch Davis]] || 8\u20133 || 6\u20131\n|-\n| [[1996 Miami Hurricanes football team|1996]]\u2020 || 9\u20133 || 6\u20131\n|-\n| [[2000 Miami Hurricanes football team|2000]] || 11\u20131 || 7\u20130\n|-\n| [[2001 Miami Hurricanes football team|2001]] || rowspan=\"3\" | [[Larry Coker]] || 12\u20130 || 7\u20130\n|-\n| [[2002 Miami Hurricanes football team|2002]] || 12\u20130 || 7\u20130\n|-\n| [[2003 Miami Hurricanes football team|2003]]\u2020 || 11\u20132 || 6\u20131\n|}\n\u2020 Co-champions\n\n===Division championships===\nMiami has one division championship in the ACC Coastal Division.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Miami Hurricanes|Year|Division|Coach|Opponent|CG result}}\n|-\n| [[2017 Miami Hurricanes football team|2017]] || ACC Coastal || [[Mark Richt]] || [[2017 Clemson Tigers football team|Clemson]] || L 3\u201338\n|}\n\n==Bowl games==\n{{main|List of Miami Hurricanes bowl games}}\nMiami has played in 41 bowl games, going 19\u201322. Its most common bowl destination has been the [[Orange Bowl (game)|Orange Bowl]], where the 'Canes have appeared 9 times and compiled a 6\u20133 record. Miami's most common opponent in bowl play has been [[Nebraska Cornhuskers football|Nebraska]]. The schools have met six times in bowl play, with the Hurricanes having a 4\u20132 record against the Cornhuskers.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Miami Hurricanes|Date|Bowl|Opponent|Result}}\n|-\n| January 1, 1935 || [[1935 Orange Bowl|Orange Bowl]] || [[Bucknell Bison|Bucknell]] || L 0\u201326\n|-\n| January 1, 1946 || [[Orange Bowl (game)|Orange Bowl]] || [[Holy Cross Crusaders football|Holy Cross]] || '''W''' 6\u201313\n|-\n| January 1, 1951 || [[Orange Bowl (game)|Orange Bowl]] || [[Clemson Tigers football|Clemson]] || L 14\u201315\n|-\n| January 1, 1952 || [[Gator Bowl]] || [[Clemson Tigers football|Clemson]] || '''W''' 0\u201314\n|-\n| December 16, 1961 || [[Liberty Bowl]] || [[1961 Syracuse Orangemen football team|Syracuse]] || L 15\u201315\n|-\n| December 15, 1962 || [[Gotham Bowl]] || [[1962 Nebraska Cornhuskers football team|Nebraska]] || L 34\u201336\n|-\n| December 10, 1966 || [[1966 Liberty Bowl|Liberty Bowl]] || [[Virginia Tech Hokies football|Virginia Tech]] || '''W''' 14\u20137\n|-\n| December 23, 1967 || [[Bluebonnet Bowl]] || [[1967 Colorado Buffaloes football team|Colorado]] || L 21\u201331\n|-\n| January 2, 1981 || [[1981 Peach Bowl (January)|Peach Bowl]] || [[Virginia Tech Hokies football|Virginia Tech]] || '''W''' 20\u201310\n|-\n| January 2, 1984 || [[1984 Orange Bowl|Orange Bowl]]<br />|| [[1983 Nebraska Cornhuskers football team|Nebraska]] || '''W''' 31\u201330\n|-\n| January 1, 1985|| [[1985 Fiesta Bowl|Fiesta Bowl]] || [[1984 UCLA Bruins football team|UCLA]] || L 37\u201339\n|-\n| January 1, 1986 || [[1986 Sugar Bowl|Sugar Bowl]] || [[1985 Tennessee Volunteers football team|Tennessee]] || L 7\u201335\n|-\n| January 2, 1987 || [[1987 Fiesta Bowl|Fiesta Bowl]] || [[1986 Penn State Nittany Lions football team|Penn State]] || L 10\u201314\n|-\n| January 1, 1988 || [[1988 Orange Bowl|Orange Bowl]] || [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma]] || '''W''' 20\u201314\n|-\n| January 2, 1989 || [[1989 Orange Bowl|Orange Bowl]] || [[1988 Nebraska Cornhuskers football team|Nebraska]] || '''W''' 23\u20133\n|-\n| January 1, 1990 || [[1990 Sugar Bowl|Sugar Bowl]] || [[1989 Alabama Crimson Tide football team|Alabama]] || '''W''' 33\u201325\n|-\n| January 1, 1991 || [[19