{"title_page": "Shah Sulaim\u0101n N\u016bri", "text_new": "{{Short description|A Famous Sufi Saint Of Qaddriyya Silsila in 16th Century}}\n<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Shah Sulaim\u0101n N\u016bri|timestamp=20200407125115|year=2020|month=April|day=7|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Shah Sulaim\u0101n N\u016bri|date=7 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n'''Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori'''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n991/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) Volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ziaetaiba.com/en/scholar/hazrat-sakhi-shah-suleman-noori|title=Hazrat Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori|website=www.ziaetaiba.com|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|url=http://archive.org/details/FAYZANENAUSHAHSecondEdition|title=FAYZAN-E NAUSHAH Second Edition}}</ref> (also known as \"Sakhi Badshah\") was a well known scholar, saint and Sufi of [[Qadiriyya]] silsila in sub-continent (Now Punjab, Pakistan). His Spirtual leader and \"Murshid\" was Syed  [[Shah Maroof Khushabi]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n991/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> He spent his whole live in devotion and love for Allah.\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Shah Suleman\n| image              = HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 4.jpg\n| birth_date         = 9TH RABI UL AWAL 1508\n| death_date         = 27TH RAMZAN UL MUBARIK FRIDAY NIGHT 1604\n| resting_place      = Purana Bhalwal,Bhalwal Sharif\n| era                = 16th Century\n| title              = Sakhi,Noori Hazoori,Shah e Shahan\n| predecessor        = Shah Maroof Khushabi\n| successor          = Nausha Ganj Baksh Ranmal Sharif\n| children           = Raheem Dad,Taj Mahmood\n| parents            = Father:Abdullah, Mother: Bhaag Bhari\n}}\n\n== Birth and parents ==\nSakhi Shah Suleman father's name was Abdullah<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\" /><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) volume 1 page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> who was also a kind and noble man and follower of Syed Shah Maroof Khushabi.His mother name was \"BIBI Bhaag Bhari\" she was also so generous and kind. Sakhi Shah Suleman was born on 9th Rabi ul Awal 1508.<ref name=\":0\" /> His Family lineage belongs to [[Quraysh]]<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Early life and education ==\nHe got his early education from his parents. Shah Maroof used to visit Abdullah\"s house.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n993/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 882|last=|first=|date=|website=Archive.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> One day Shah Maroof Khushabi visited Shah Suleman's house.At that time Sakhi Shah Suleman was 4 year old.Shah Suleman was playing in front yard.He identified Shah Suleman as his successor and the cause for which he was sent to this town.He called Shah Suleman and kissed his forehead.He then asked his father to keep Shah Suleman in protection as he is his entrustment.His Spirtual progress started in his childhood<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n993/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628|website=archive.org|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>.\n\n== Personal life ==\nSakhi Shah Suleman had two wives:\n\n# Bibi Romal Khatun\n# Bibi Jaurana Khatun<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1017/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 904|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nHe had two sons:\n\n# Raheem Daad\n# Taaj Mehmood<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1017/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 905-6|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n== Family Lineage ==\n'''''Ka'ab ul Qarshi \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Marra \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Qilab  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''[[Qusai ibn Kilab|Qusai]] \u2935'''''\n\n'''''[[Abd al-Uzza ibn Qusai|Abd al-Uzza]] \u2935'''''\n\n'''''[[Asad ibn Abd al-Uzza|Asad]] \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Muttalib \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Aswad \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Habbar\u2935'''''\n\n'''''Ameer Abdur Rehman\u2935'''''\n\n'''''Ameer Abdur Raheem\u2935'''''\n\n'''''Mautrif \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Khadim \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Khazeema \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Taj Uddin Mautrif \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdul A'ala \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdul Shakoor \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Adam \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Mazhar  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Ismael  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Qasim  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Aon \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Sultan Ali \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Khuda Yar \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdul Khaliq \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Sheikh Hussain \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Muhammad Saleh \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Muhammad Murad \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Shams Uddin \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Jalal Uddin  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdullah  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori''''' <ref>{{Cite book|url=http://archive.org/details/family-lineage-of-shah-suleman-nuri|title=Family Lineage Of Sakhi Shah Suleman Nuri|language=Khasi}}</ref>\n\n== Spiritual Lineage ==\nHe got his spiritual teachings from Shah Maroof Khushabi.\n\nHe belonged to Silsila e Qadriyya as below:\n\n* [[Muhammad]] pbuh\n* [[Ali]]\n* [[Hasan al-Basri]]\n* [[Habib al-Ajami]]\n* [[Dawud Tai]]\n* [[Maruf Karkhi]]\n* [[Sirri Saqti]]\n* [[Junayd of Baghdad]]\n* [[Abu Bakr Shibli]]\n* [[Abdul Aziz bin Hars bin Asad Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Abu Al Fazal Abdul Wahid Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Mohammad Yousuf Abu al-Farah Tartusi]]\n* [[Abul Hasan Hankari]]\n* [[Abu Saeed Mubarak Makhzoomi]]\n* [[Abdul Qadir Gilani]]\n* Syed Abdul Wahab Gilani\n*Syed Abdul Salam Gilani\n* \n* Syed Ahmad Gilani\n* Syed Masood Gilani\n* Syed Ali Gilani\n* Syed Shahmeer Gilani\n* Shams Uddin Gilani\n* Shah Muhammad Ghoas Gilani\n* Syed Mubarak Haqani Gilani Uch Sharif\n*[[Shah Maroof Khushabi|Shah Maroof Farooqi Chisti Qadri]]\n* Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Teaching and characteristics ==\nWhen Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori received the \"KHILAFAT\", He was ordered by his \"Murshid\" to travel different places.So he travelled [[Shahpur]],[[Khushab]],[[Chawa]],Deowal,Jukali, Takht Hazaara,Kashmir AND Gujrat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n997/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 887|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Thousand of non Muslims became Muslims on his hands.After travel,his sheikh ordered him to reside in Purana Bhalwal (Now in tehsil Bhalwal,District Sargodha).Thousand of people from surrounding found straight way from them.\n\nSakhi Shah Suleman was strict follower of Shariat and Sunnat e Muhummad.He spent his mostly time in mosque in remembrance of Allah\n\nHe was so generous that he got the title of \"Sakhi\" .He was very kind to poors and needy ones.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1003/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 892|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n== Successors ==\nThere are many successors of Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori.Some of them are known and some are unknown<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1019/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 906|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nHis known successors are following:\n\n# [[Muhammad Qadiri]]: He was Sakhi Shah Suleman's beloved successor who founded the Silsila \"Qadria Naushahia\".\n# Raheem Dad : He was the elder son of Sakhi Shah Suleman and \"Sajaada e Nasheen\".\n# Taj Mehmood: He was the younger son of Sakhi Shah Suleman.\n# Mullah Kareem Uddin Jokalvi\n# Dewan Abu Al Fatah Kanboh\n# Mullah Ghazi Gondal Bhalwali\n# Sheikh Hammo Faqeer\n# Sheikh Hindi<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\" />\n\n== Shrine ==\n[[File:HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 2.jpg|thumb|DARBAR SHARIF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI]]\nSakhi Shah Suleman blessed shrine in located in [[Purana Bhalwal]],district Sargodha<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1025/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 912|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.qadri-naushahi.com/Awliya/Genealogy2.html|title=Genealogy & Spiritual Lineage No. 25|last=|first=|date=|website=www.qadri-naushahi.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auqaf.punjab.gov.pk/shrines#sargodha|title=Shrines {{!}} Auqaf & Religious Affairs Department|website=auqaf.punjab.gov.pk|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/Darbaar+Sakhi+Shah+Sulman+Noori+Hazoori/@32.2730345,72.8739842,17.83z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x3921a295ec3eff79:0x91434f6ac5759c18!8m2!3d32.2728078!4d72.8745575?shorturl=1|title=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|website=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>.The central big blessed grave is of Sakhi Shah Suleman while the 1st grave on the right side is of Abdul Wahid bin Raheem Dad bin Shah Suleman.The 2nd grave on right side is of Raheem Dad bin Shah Suleman.On the left hand,the 1st grave is of Abdul Wahab bin Taj Mahmood bin Shah Suleman while the 2nd grave is of Taj Mahmood bin Shah Suleman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1025/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 912-13|last=|first=|date=|website=archive.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>.\n\n== Death ==\nSakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori died on night of friday 27th Ramzan ul Mubaraik 1604.He died at the age of 96 years<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Sufism in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Qadiri order]]\n[[Category:Islam-related lists]]\n[[Category:Sufi literature]]\n__INDEX__\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|A Famous Sufi Saint Of Qaddriyya Silsila in 16th Century}}\n<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Shah Sulaim\u0101n N\u016bri|timestamp=20200407125115|year=2020|month=April|day=7|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Shah Sulaim\u0101n N\u016bri|date=7 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n'''Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori'''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n991/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) Volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ziaetaiba.com/en/scholar/hazrat-sakhi-shah-suleman-noori|title=Hazrat Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori|website=www.ziaetaiba.com|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|url=http://archive.org/details/FAYZANENAUSHAHSecondEdition|title=FAYZAN-E NAUSHAH Second Edition}}</ref> (also known as \"Sakhi Badshah\") was a well known scholar, saint and Sufi of [[Qadiriyya]] silsila in sub-continent (Now Punjab, Pakistan). His Spirtual leader and \"Murshid\" was Syed  [[Shah Maroof Khushabi]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) volume 1 Page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n991/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 881|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> He spent his whole live in devotion and love for Allah.\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Shah Suleman\n| image              = HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 4.jpg\n| birth_date         = 9TH RABI UL AWAL 1508\n| death_date         = 27TH RAMZAN UL MUBARIK FRIDAY NIGHT 1604\n| resting_place      = Purana Bhalwal,Bhalwal Sharif\n| era                = 16th Century\n| title              = Sakhi,Noori Hazoori,Shah e Shahan\n| predecessor        = Shah Maroof Khushabi\n| successor          = Nausha Ganj Baksh Ranmal Sharif\n| children           = Raheem Dad,Taj Mahmood\n| parents            = Father:Abdullah, Mother: Bhaag Bhari\n}}\n\n== Birth and parents ==\nSakhi Shah Suleman father's name was Abdullah<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 881\" /><ref>{{Cite book|last=Mufti Ghulam Sarwar Lahori|url=http://archive.org/details/Khazinat-ul-asfiyaurduTranslation4Volumes|title=Khazinat-ul-Asfiya (Urdu translation) volume 1 page 254|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> who was also a kind and noble man and follower of Syed Shah Maroof Khushabi.His mother name was \"BIBI Bhaag Bhari\" she was also so generous and kind. Sakhi Shah Suleman was born on 9th Rabi ul Awal 1508.<ref name=\":0\" /> His Family lineage belongs to [[Quraysh]]<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Early life and education ==\nHe got his early education from his parents. Shah Maroof used to visit Abdullah\"s house.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n993/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 882|last=|first=|date=|website=Archive.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> One day Shah Maroof Khushabi visited Shah Suleman's house.At that time Sakhi Shah Suleman was 4 year old.Shah Suleman was playing in front yard.He identified Shah Suleman as his successor and the cause for which he was sent to this town.He called Shah Suleman and kissed his forehead.He then asked his father to keep Shah Suleman in protection as he is his entrustment.His Spirtual progress started in his childhood<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n993/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628|website=archive.org|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>.\n\n== Personal life ==\nSakhi Shah Suleman had two wives:\n\n# Bibi Romal Khatun\n# Bibi Jaurana Khatun<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1017/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 904|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nHe had two sons:\n\n# Raheem Daad\n# Taaj Mehmood<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1017/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 905-6|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n== Family Lineage ==\n'''''Ka'ab ul Qarshi \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Marra \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Qilab  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''[[Qusai ibn Kilab|Qusai]] \u2935'''''\n\n'''''[[Abd al-Uzza ibn Qusai|Abd al-Uzza]] \u2935'''''\n\n'''''[[Asad ibn Abd al-Uzza|Asad]] \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Muttalib \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Aswad \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Habbar\u2935'''''\n\n'''''Ameer Abdur Rehman\u2935'''''\n\n'''''Ameer Abdur Raheem\u2935'''''\n\n'''''Mautrif \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Khadim \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Khazeema \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Taj Uddin Mautrif \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdul A'ala \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdul Shakoor \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Adam \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Mazhar  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Ismael  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Qasim  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Aon \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Sultan Ali \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Khuda Yar \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdul Khaliq \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Sheikh Hussain \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Muhammad Saleh \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Muhammad Murad \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Shams Uddin \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Jalal Uddin  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Abdullah  \u2935'''''\n\n'''''Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori''''' <ref>{{Cite book|url=http://archive.org/details/family-lineage-of-shah-suleman-nuri|title=Family Lineage Of Sakhi Shah Suleman Nuri|language=Khasi}}</ref>\n\n== Spiritual Lineage ==\nHe got his spiritual teachings from Shah Maroof Khushabi.\n\nHe belonged to Silsila e Qadriyya as below:\n\n* [[Muhammad]] pbuh\n* [[Ali]]\n* [[Hasan al-Basri]]\n* [[Habib al-Ajami]]\n* [[Dawud Tai]]\n* [[Maruf Karkhi]]\n* [[Sirri Saqti]]\n* [[Junayd of Baghdad]]\n* [[Abu Bakr Shibli]]\n* [[Abdul Aziz bin Hars bin Asad Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Abu Al Fazal Abdul Wahid Yemeni Tamimi]]\n* [[Mohammad Yousuf Abu al-Farah Tartusi]]\n* [[Abul Hasan Hankari]]\n* [[Abu Saeed Mubarak Makhzoomi]]\n* [[Abdul Qadir Gilani]]\n* Syed Abdul Wahab Gilani\n*Syed Abdul Salam Gilani\n* \n* Syed Ahmad Gilani\n* Syed Masood Gilani\n* Syed Ali Gilani\n* Syed Shahmeer Gilani\n* Shams Uddin Gilani\n* Shah Muhammad Ghoas Gilani\n* Syed Mubarak Haqani Gilani Uch Sharif\n*[[Shah Maroof Khushabi|Shah Maroof Farooqi Chisti Qadri]]\n* SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Teaching and characteristics ==\nWhen Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori received the \"KHILAFAT\", He was ordered by his \"Murshid\" to travel different places.So he travelled [[Shahpur]],[[Khushab]],[[Chawa]],Deowal,Jukali, Takht Hazaara,Kashmir AND Gujrat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n997/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 887|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Thousand of non Muslims became Muslims on his hands.After travel,his sheikh ordered him to reside in Purana Bhalwal (Now in tehsil Bhalwal,District Sargodha).Thousand of people from surrounding found straight way from them.\n\nSakhi Shah Suleman was strict follower of Shariat and Sunnat e Muhummad.He spent his mostly time in mosque in remembrance of Allah\n\nHe was so generous that he got the title of \"Sakhi\" .He was very kind to poors and needy ones.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1003/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 892|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n== Successors ==\nThere are many successors of Sakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori.Some of them are known and some are unknown<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1019/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 906|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nHis known successors are following:\n\n# [[Muhammad Qadiri]]: He was Sakhi Shah Suleman's beloved successor who founded the Silsila \"Qadria Naushahia\".\n# Raheem Dad : He was the elder son of Sakhi Shah Suleman and \"Sajaada e Nasheen\".\n# Taj Mehmood: He was the younger son of Sakhi Shah Suleman.\n# Mullah Kareem Uddin Jokalvi\n# Dewan Abu Al Fatah Kanboh\n# Mullah Ghazi Gondal Bhalwali\n# Sheikh Hammo Faqeer\n# Sheikh Hindi<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 906\" />\n\n== Shrine ==\n[[File:HAZRAT SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN 2.jpg|thumb|DARBAR SHARIF SAKHI SHAH SULEMAN NOORI HAZOORI]]\nSakhi Shah Suleman blessed shrine in located in [[Purana Bhalwal]],district Sargodha<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\">{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1025/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 912|last=|first=|date=|website=Archieve.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.qadri-naushahi.com/Awliya/Genealogy2.html|title=Genealogy & Spiritual Lineage No. 25|last=|first=|date=|website=www.qadri-naushahi.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auqaf.punjab.gov.pk/shrines#sargodha|title=Shrines {{!}} Auqaf & Religious Affairs Department|website=auqaf.punjab.gov.pk|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/Darbaar+Sakhi+Shah+Sulman+Noori+Hazoori/@32.2730345,72.8739842,17.83z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x3921a295ec3eff79:0x91434f6ac5759c18!8m2!3d32.2728078!4d72.8745575?shorturl=1|title=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|website=Darbaar Sakhi Shah Sulman Noori Hazoori|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>.The central big blessed grave is of Sakhi Shah Suleman while the 1st grave on the right side is of Abdul Wahid bin Raheem Dad bin Shah Suleman.The 2nd grave on right side is of Raheem Dad bin Shah Suleman.On the left hand,the 1st grave is of Abdul Wahab bin Taj Mahmood bin Shah Suleman while the 2nd grave is of Taj Mahmood bin Shah Suleman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/SharifUtTawarikhTareekhUlAqtaab/Sharif%20Ut%20Tawarikh%20Tareekh%20Ul%20Aqtaab%20#page/n1025/mode/2up|title=Sharif Ut Tawarikh Tareekh Ul Aqtaab / \u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062a\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0628 Page 912-13|last=|first=|date=|website=archive.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>.\n\n== Death ==\nSakhi Shah Suleman Noori Hazoori died on night of friday 27th Ramzan ul Mubaraik 1604.He died at the age of 96 years<ref name=\"\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u0627\u0631\u06cc\u062e \u062c\u0644\u062f 1.pdf Page 912\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Sufism in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Qadiri order]]\n[[Category:Islam-related lists]]\n[[Category:Sufi literature]]\n__INDEX__\n", "name_user": "Saadulhassan2", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shah_Sulaim%C4%81n_N%C5%ABri"}
{"title_page": "Dave Dresden", "text_new": "<!--NOTE TO EDITORS: Please do not add unverifiable rumors and speculation to the article. \nAlso, please visit the discussion page before adding large portions of content.-->\n{{Infobox musical artist|<!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians and Template:Infobox_musical_artist -->\n| name             = Dave Dresden\n| caption          = Dresden performing with [[Gabriel & Dresden]] at [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella Festival]] in 2006.\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = Dave \"The Wave\" Dresden\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1969|5|20}}\n| death_date       = \n| origin           = [[Stamford, Connecticut]], United States\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = [[Progressive trance]], [[House music|house]], [[Electronic dance music|EDM]]\n| occupation       = [[Disc jockey|DJ]], [[Record producer|producer]], [[remix]]er, [[A&R]], [[music director]], [[journalist]]\n| years_active     = 1988&ndash;present\n| label            = [[Organized Nature]], Problem Child\n| associated_acts  = [[Dresden & Johnston]], [[Gabriel & Dresden]], Motorcycle, [[Andain]]. Summit, A.llison D.resden D.uo, Attention Deficit, Bigtop, The Consumers, [[Morgan Page]]\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Dave Dresden''' is an American [[electronic dance music]] DJ and producer, co-founder of the collaborative acts [[Gabriel & Dresden]] with [[Josh Gabriel]], and [[Dresden and Johnston]] with [[Mikael Johnston]].\n\n==History==\n\n===1988\u20132000: Early years===\nDresden's zeal for dance music and culture developed early in high school where he frequented local [[Connecticut]] dance clubs and befriended The Caf\u00e9's DJ [[Moby]], a local disc jockey. His early experiences at the Caf\u00e9 fueled his passion to immerse himself in the culture that would become his career and lifelong obsession. From there, he purchased a pair of [[Technics (brand)|Technics SP-1300]] pitch controlled CD players and got to work.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dancemusic.about.com/od/remixersproducers/a/DaveDresdenInt_2.htm |title=Dave Dresden Interview - Gabriel and Dresden 2008 Interview |publisher=Dancemusic.about.com |date=2014-03-04 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Dresden quickly cultivated a following due to his simple but effective music policy; play the right track at the right time and only play great songs. His ambitions did not stop with spinning. While he continued to play in the clubs sometimes five nights a week, he became a dance music journalist by day. Dresden was named a reporter to the Billboard dance chart, and he began writing reviews and features for national magazines such as ''Dance Music Authority'', ''[[DJ Times]]'' and ''Mixer''. Dresden profiled [[Daft Punk]], [[Paul Oakenfold]], [[Moby]], [[Masters at Work]], [[Todd Terry]], [[Sasha & Digweed]], [[Puff Daddy]], [[BT (musician)|BT]], [[Crystal Method]], [[Keoki]], [[Josh Wink]], [[Chemical Brothers]], [[Deep Dish (band)|Deep Dish]] amongst many others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dancemusic.about.com/cs/features/a/DaveWaveBio.htm |title=Dave \"the Wave\" Dresden Interviews |publisher=Dancemusic.about.com |date=2014-03-04 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Many of these artists' first American press came through Dresden's journalism efforts.\n\nDresden's affiliation with respected publications gave him easier access to obscure and unreleased tunes upfront, giving him an edge. He regularly contributed his A&R skills to Promo Only CD's and its \"Mainstream Club\" \"Import Club\" and \"Alternative Club\" series. In addition, he scouted new music for Pete Tong's highly influential [[Essential Selection]] radio show on the [[BBC Radio 1]]. Through his efforts there, Dresden hipped Pete to some rather large records, many of which became \"Essential New Tunes\", Tong's method of gauging a guaranteed hit. Dresden's wide knowledge of dance music led to the opportunity to help select songs for [[Nettwerk]] Records' popular \"Plastic Compilation\" series. Dresden has also had a hand in producing compilation CD's and single releases with other independent labels such as Strictly Rhythm, Strictly Hype, 4 Play and Max Music. In addition, he's accredited by his own releases for Strictly Hype's trance offshoot Sunrise; \"Trancendence: The First Wave\", and the hit packed \"Transit\". His radio career began with the long running, highly rated \"Electro Circus,\" which aired on [[Hartford, Connecticut]]'s modern rock station [[WMRQ-FM]] from 1996 until 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fundjforyou.com/rcdj/basement/thewave.html |title=Dave the wave's radio program |publisher=Fundjforyou.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Dresden's radio career continued as music director and on-air personality for grooveradio.com, an [[internet radio station]] during the year 2000.\n\n===2001\u20132008: Gabriel & Dresden===\n{{Main|Gabriel & Dresden}}\nIn 2000 Dave became the [[Music Director]] of [[Swedish Egil]]'s grooveradio.com where he met [[Pete Tong]], who asked him to help find music for the [[Essential Selection]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.davepearce.co.uk/interviews/gabriel_and_dresden/ |title=The Official Dave Pearce Website - Interviews > Gabriel & Dresden |publisher=Davepearce.co.uk |date=1999-12-04 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> They met at a party being hosted by grooveradio.com at the [[Miami]] [[Winter Music Conference]] in March 2001. [[Josh Gabriel]] gave Leon Alexander a record, the record was \"Wave 3\", which Dave then gave to Pete Tong, and he played it on the Essential Selection and also used it for his compilation that same year. Pete gave Dave the opportunity to do a remix of [[New Order (band)|New Order]] [[Someone Like You (New Order song)|Someone Like You]] and Dave asked Josh to work on it with him. The two joined forces in 2001 and made a name for themselves by creating numerous remixes for artists as diverse as [[Ti\u00ebsto]], [[Paul Oakenfold]], [[Sarah Mclachlan]], [[Way Out West (duo)|Way Out West]], [[Annie Lennox]], [[Duncan Sheik]], and [[Jewel (singer)]].\n\nIn 2002 Gabriel & Dresden released their first single \"Lament\" [[Saw Recordings]] in the United States. The duo released numerous singles and number one ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' hits like \"[[As the Rush Comes]]\" (as [[Motorcycle (band)|Motorcycle]], \"[[Tracking Treasure Down]]\" and \"[[Dangerous Power]]\"; they also released one self-titled studio album together, ''[[Gabriel & Dresden (album)|Gabriel & Dresden]]'' which was named as the \"2006 Album of the Year\" by M8 magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.residentadvisor.net/forum-read.aspx?id=56273 |title=RA: Made Event presents Dave Dresden at Cielo, New York (2009) |publisher=Residentadvisor.net |date=2009-01-22 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref>\n\nThe duo won the 2007 and 2008 IDMA award for \"America's Best DJ\". He has achieved 21 Billboard Dance Chart #1 tracks (remixes and originals) as \"Gabriel & Dresden\", composed music that has appeared on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]], [[HBO]], [[NBC]] and [[CBS]] TV shows. Gabriel & Dresden have their own record label, [[Organized Nature]] which is distributed by [[Armada Music]].\n\n===2009\u20132010: Solo years===\nAfter the break-up of Gabriel & Dresden, Dave collaborated with [[Chris Cox (DJ)|Chris Cox]] on a track called \"Whole Wide World\", which was played on Pete Tong's Essential Selection on April 4, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/petetong/tracklistingarchive.shtml?20080418 |title=Radio 1 - Pete Tong - Tracklisting |publisher=BBC |date= |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Dave also worked with Trent Cantrelle on a remix for Serge Devant's cover of [[The Beloved (band)|the Beloved]]'s \"[[Sweet Harmony (The Beloved song)|Sweet Harmony]]\". On June 22, Dave opened a set for [[Ti\u00ebsto]]'s [[In Search of Sunrise: North American Summer Tour 2008]] in [[Connecticut]]. He also co-wrote and co-produced \"I've Had Friends\" with [[Morgan Page]] which was the 4th single from his album [[Believe (Morgan Page album)]]\n\nIn December 2008, Dresden teamed up with longtime friend and [[Mephisto Odyssey]] founder Mikael Johnston to remix [[Lily Allen]]'s \"The Fear\" under the new moniker [[Dresden and Johnston]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beatportal.com/feed/item/dave-dresden-reveals-new-partnership/ |title=Beatport News - Daily music news, reviews, interviews, and culture for the DJ and producer |publisher=Beatportal.com |date=2014-07-15 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> The new production duo went on to remix a number of artists including [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]]'s \"Love Story\" and [[Enrique Iglesias]]'s \"[[Tonight (I'm Fuckin' You)]]\", all of which hit the #1 position in [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] Chart. [[Dresden and Johnston]]'s first original single called \"Keep Faith\" Featuring Mezo Riccio followed in early 2010 and went to #10 in [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] chart and top 5 on Sirius radio's [[BPM (Sirius XM)]] and [[Club Phusion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beatportal.com/feed/item/beatport-exclusive-dresden-johnston-release-keep-faith/ |title=Beatport News - Daily music news, reviews, interviews, and culture for the DJ and producer |publisher=Beatportal.com |date=2014-07-15 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> The single featured remixes by fellow producers [[Morgan Page]] and [[Harry Romero]]. A forthcoming full-length album by the duo featuring guest vocalists [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]], [[Jan Burton]] and [[Skylar Grey]] was planned but is yet to be released.\n\n=== Gabriel & Dresden reunion (2011\u2013present)===\nOn December 31, 2010, Gabriel & Dresden reunited for special one off New Year's Eve celebration alongside [[ATB]] and Francis Preve at the [[Hollywood Palladium]] in Los Angeles.\n\nShortly afterward, the duo were booked on the [[Anjunabeats]] WMC Miami party at the Ice Palace as a special guest. Since this event, Gabriel & Dresden have officially announced themselves as reunited.\n\nSince the reunion, Gabriel & Dresden have performed at many clubs and festivals around the world including [[Electric Daisy Carnival]] (Las Vegas, Dallas, Chicago & Orlando), [[Tomorrowland (festival)|Tomorrowland]] in Belgium, [[Electric Zoo Festival]] in New York, [[Sunburn Festival]] in India, [[Beyond Wonderland|Escape From Wonderland]], [[Nocturnal Wonderland]], [[Paradiso Festival]], [[Creamfields Australia]], [[A State of Trance|ASOT 550: Invasion]], [[Ministry of Sound]], London, [[Zouk (club)|Zouk]] and a monthly residency at the [[Jason Strauss|Marquee Las Vegas]] in Las Vegas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bandsintown.com/GabrielAndDresden/past_events |title=Gabriel & Dresden Tour History from 2007 - 2014 - Gabriel & Dresden Past Tour Dates |publisher=Bandsintown.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011 they signed an artist deal with [[Armada Music]] which brought forth their mix compilation \"Mixed for Feet, Volume 1\" as well as numerous singles including 2012'a \"Play it Back\" featuring [[Betsie Larkin]], \"Tomorrow Comes\" with Neil Ormandy (2013), \"Shatter\" (with D-Wayne) and a re-working of [[Tracking Treasure Down|Tracking Treasure Down Revisited]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2011/12/we-welcome-gabriel-dresdens-organized-nature-label/ |title=\u00ab Armada Music |publisher=Armadamusic.com |date=2011-12-08 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref>\n\nOn February 3, 2014, they restarted their monthly radio show \"Gabriel & Dresden present [[Organized Nature]]\" on [[Digitally Imported]]'s progressive channel. Since this show was already on the air in the past, it began this time around with Episode 30.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.di.fm/calendar/event/36131 |title=Organized Nature - with Gabriel & Dresden - DI Radio |publisher=Di.fm |accessdate=2014-08-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140618110918/http://www.di.fm/calendar/event/36131 |archivedate=2014-06-18 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGraduated in class of 88' from Westhill High School in Stamford, Connecticut.\n\nDresden got married in September 2012 to Holly Carrington. They have one daughter together, Charlotte Lily Dresden born on July 15, 2013. They filed for divorce in 2017 and the divorce was finalized in Austin, Texas on July 3, 2018.\n\n==Discography==\n''For discography as [[Gabriel & Dresden]], see [[Gabriel & Dresden#Discography|Gabriel & Dresden discography]].''<br />\n''For awards as [[Gabriel & Dresden]], see [[Gabriel & Dresden#Awards and nominations|Gabriel & Dresden Awards / Nominations]].''\n\n===Singles===\n*[[New Gold Dream]] (81-82-83-84) as The Consumers (with [[Dave Ralph]])\n*Use Only The Drugs (as Attention Deficit) 2003\n*Goddess <small>(as Summit)</small> 2004\n*[[Chris Cox (DJ)|Chris Cox]] & Dave Dresden - Whole Wide World 2008 (unreleased)\n*[[Morgan Page]] & Dave Dresden - I've Had Friends <small>(feat. [[Jan Burton]])</small> 2008 \n*Dave Dresden & Grayarea - Cloud Atlas 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] vs. Debo ft. Mezo - Keep Faith 2010 (released) Problem Child Rekords\n*Dave Dresden, [[Super 8 & Tab]] - Black Ice 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - That Day <small>(feat. [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]])</small> 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - I Hear You Calling <small>(feat. David Penner & Essence)</small> 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - Racecar (feat [[Holly Brook]]) 2010 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - Undertow (feat [[Holly Brook]]) 2010 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - I Know You (Feat [[Holly Brook]]) 2010 (unreleased)\n\n===Remixes===\n*[[Lily Allen]] The Fear <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> 2009\n*[[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]] Love Story <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> 2009\n*[[BT (musician)|BT]] The Unbreakable <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> (unreleased)\n*[[JD Webb]] Better Man <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> 2009\n*[[The Crystal Method]] Black Rainbows <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small>\n*[[Enrique Iglesias]] feat. [[Ludacris]] Tonight <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small>\n*[[Morgan Page & Dave Dresden]] I've Had Friends <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> (unreleased)\n*[[Linkin Park]] Waiting For The End <small> (as Dave Dresden) </small>\n\n===Compilations===\n* Trancendence - The First Wave 2000\n* Transit 200\n* Provocative Progressive 2002\n\n===Co-productions===\n* [[Armin van Buuren]] - Zocalo\n* [[Markus Schulz]] - Without You Near\n* [[Christina Aguilera]] - [[Hurt (Christina Aguilera song)]] <small>(Chris Cox Club Anthem)</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://myspace.com/davedresden Dave Dresden] on [[Myspace]]\n{{Gabriel & Dresden}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dresden, Dave}}\n[[Category:American record producers]]\n[[Category:Remixers]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American trance musicians]]\n[[Category:American DJs]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n", "text_old": "<!--NOTE TO EDITORS: Please do not add unverifiable rumors and speculation to the article. \nAlso, please visit the discussion page before adding large portions of content.-->\n{{Infobox musical artist|<!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians and Template:Infobox_musical_artist -->\n| name             = Dave Dresden\n| caption          = Dresden performing with [[Gabriel & Dresden]] at [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella Festival]] in 2006.\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| birth_name       = \n| alias            = Dave \"The Wave\" Dresden\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1969|5|20}}\n| death_date       = \n| origin           = [[Stamford, Connecticut]], United States\n| instrument       = \n| genre            = [[Progressive trance]], [[House music|house]], [[Electronic dance music|EDM]]\n| occupation       = [[Disc jockey|DJ]], [[Record producer|producer]], [[remix]]er, [[A&R]], [[music director]], [[journalist]]\n| years_active     = 1988&ndash;present\n| label            = [[Organized Nature]], Problem Child\n| associated_acts  = [[Dresden & Johnston]], [[Gabriel & Dresden]], [[Motorcycle]], [[Andain]]. Summit, A.llison D.resden D.uo, Attention Deficit, Bigtop, The Consumers, [[Morgan Page]]\n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Dave Dresden''' is an American [[electronic dance music]] DJ and producer, co-founder of the collaborative acts [[Gabriel & Dresden]] with [[Josh Gabriel]], and [[Dresden and Johnston]] with [[Mikael Johnston]].\n\n==History==\n\n===1988\u20132000: Early years===\nDresden's zeal for dance music and culture developed early in high school where he frequented local [[Connecticut]] dance clubs and befriended The Caf\u00e9's DJ [[Moby]], a local disc jockey. His early experiences at the Caf\u00e9 fueled his passion to immerse himself in the culture that would become his career and lifelong obsession. From there, he purchased a pair of [[Technics (brand)|Technics SP-1300]] pitch controlled CD players and got to work.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dancemusic.about.com/od/remixersproducers/a/DaveDresdenInt_2.htm |title=Dave Dresden Interview - Gabriel and Dresden 2008 Interview |publisher=Dancemusic.about.com |date=2014-03-04 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Dresden quickly cultivated a following due to his simple but effective music policy; play the right track at the right time and only play great songs. His ambitions did not stop with spinning. While he continued to play in the clubs sometimes five nights a week, he became a dance music journalist by day. Dresden was named a reporter to the Billboard dance chart, and he began writing reviews and features for national magazines such as ''Dance Music Authority'', ''[[DJ Times]]'' and ''Mixer''. Dresden profiled [[Daft Punk]], [[Paul Oakenfold]], [[Moby]], [[Masters at Work]], [[Todd Terry]], [[Sasha & Digweed]], [[Puff Daddy]], [[BT (musician)|BT]], [[Crystal Method]], [[Keoki]], [[Josh Wink]], [[Chemical Brothers]], [[Deep Dish (band)|Deep Dish]] amongst many others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dancemusic.about.com/cs/features/a/DaveWaveBio.htm |title=Dave \"the Wave\" Dresden Interviews |publisher=Dancemusic.about.com |date=2014-03-04 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Many of these artists' first American press came through Dresden's journalism efforts.\n\nDresden's affiliation with respected publications gave him easier access to obscure and unreleased tunes upfront, giving him an edge. He regularly contributed his A&R skills to Promo Only CD's and its \"Mainstream Club\" \"Import Club\" and \"Alternative Club\" series. In addition, he scouted new music for Pete Tong's highly influential [[Essential Selection]] radio show on the [[BBC Radio 1]]. Through his efforts there, Dresden hipped Pete to some rather large records, many of which became \"Essential New Tunes\", Tong's method of gauging a guaranteed hit. Dresden's wide knowledge of dance music led to the opportunity to help select songs for [[Nettwerk]] Records' popular \"Plastic Compilation\" series. Dresden has also had a hand in producing compilation CD's and single releases with other independent labels such as Strictly Rhythm, Strictly Hype, 4 Play and Max Music. In addition, he's accredited by his own releases for Strictly Hype's trance offshoot Sunrise; \"Trancendence: The First Wave\", and the hit packed \"Transit\". His radio career began with the long running, highly rated \"Electro Circus,\" which aired on [[Hartford, Connecticut]]'s modern rock station [[WMRQ-FM]] from 1996 until 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fundjforyou.com/rcdj/basement/thewave.html |title=Dave the wave's radio program |publisher=Fundjforyou.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Dresden's radio career continued as music director and on-air personality for grooveradio.com, an [[internet radio station]] during the year 2000.\n\n===2001\u20132008: Gabriel & Dresden===\n{{Main|Gabriel & Dresden}}\nIn 2000 Dave became the [[Music Director]] of [[Swedish Egil]]'s grooveradio.com where he met [[Pete Tong]], who asked him to help find music for the [[Essential Selection]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.davepearce.co.uk/interviews/gabriel_and_dresden/ |title=The Official Dave Pearce Website - Interviews > Gabriel & Dresden |publisher=Davepearce.co.uk |date=1999-12-04 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> They met at a party being hosted by grooveradio.com at the [[Miami]] [[Winter Music Conference]] in March 2001. [[Josh Gabriel]] gave Leon Alexander a record, the record was \"Wave 3\", which Dave then gave to Pete Tong, and he played it on the Essential Selection and also used it for his compilation that same year. Pete gave Dave the opportunity to do a remix of [[New Order (band)|New Order]] [[Someone Like You (New Order song)|Someone Like You]] and Dave asked Josh to work on it with him. The two joined forces in 2001 and made a name for themselves by creating numerous remixes for artists as diverse as [[Ti\u00ebsto]], [[Paul Oakenfold]], [[Sarah Mclachlan]], [[Way Out West (duo)|Way Out West]], [[Annie Lennox]], [[Duncan Sheik]], and [[Jewel (singer)]].\n\nIn 2002 Gabriel & Dresden released their first single \"Lament\" [[Saw Recordings]] in the United States. The duo released numerous singles and number one ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' hits like \"[[As the Rush Comes]]\" (as [[Motorcycle (band)|Motorcycle]], \"[[Tracking Treasure Down]]\" and \"[[Dangerous Power]]\"; they also released one self-titled studio album together, ''[[Gabriel & Dresden (album)|Gabriel & Dresden]]'' which was named as the \"2006 Album of the Year\" by M8 magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.residentadvisor.net/forum-read.aspx?id=56273 |title=RA: Made Event presents Dave Dresden at Cielo, New York (2009) |publisher=Residentadvisor.net |date=2009-01-22 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref>\n\nThe duo won the 2007 and 2008 IDMA award for \"America's Best DJ\". He has achieved 21 Billboard Dance Chart #1 tracks (remixes and originals) as \"Gabriel & Dresden\", composed music that has appeared on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]], [[HBO]], [[NBC]] and [[CBS]] TV shows. Gabriel & Dresden have their own record label, [[Organized Nature]] which is distributed by [[Armada Music]].\n\n===2009\u20132010: Solo years===\nAfter the break-up of Gabriel & Dresden, Dave collaborated with [[Chris Cox (DJ)|Chris Cox]] on a track called \"Whole Wide World\", which was played on Pete Tong's Essential Selection on April 4, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio1/petetong/tracklistingarchive.shtml?20080418 |title=Radio 1 - Pete Tong - Tracklisting |publisher=BBC |date= |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> Dave also worked with Trent Cantrelle on a remix for Serge Devant's cover of [[The Beloved (band)|the Beloved]]'s \"[[Sweet Harmony (The Beloved song)|Sweet Harmony]]\". On June 22, Dave opened a set for [[Ti\u00ebsto]]'s [[In Search of Sunrise: North American Summer Tour 2008]] in [[Connecticut]]. He also co-wrote and co-produced \"I've Had Friends\" with [[Morgan Page]] which was the 4th single from his album [[Believe (Morgan Page album)]]\n\nIn December 2008, Dresden teamed up with longtime friend and [[Mephisto Odyssey]] founder Mikael Johnston to remix [[Lily Allen]]'s \"The Fear\" under the new moniker [[Dresden and Johnston]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beatportal.com/feed/item/dave-dresden-reveals-new-partnership/ |title=Beatport News - Daily music news, reviews, interviews, and culture for the DJ and producer |publisher=Beatportal.com |date=2014-07-15 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> The new production duo went on to remix a number of artists including [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]]'s \"Love Story\" and [[Enrique Iglesias]]'s \"[[Tonight (I'm Fuckin' You)]]\", all of which hit the #1 position in [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] Chart. [[Dresden and Johnston]]'s first original single called \"Keep Faith\" Featuring Mezo Riccio followed in early 2010 and went to #10 in [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] chart and top 5 on Sirius radio's [[BPM (Sirius XM)]] and [[Club Phusion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beatportal.com/feed/item/beatport-exclusive-dresden-johnston-release-keep-faith/ |title=Beatport News - Daily music news, reviews, interviews, and culture for the DJ and producer |publisher=Beatportal.com |date=2014-07-15 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref> The single featured remixes by fellow producers [[Morgan Page]] and [[Harry Romero]]. A forthcoming full-length album by the duo featuring guest vocalists [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]], [[Jan Burton]] and [[Skylar Grey]] was planned but is yet to be released.\n\n=== Gabriel & Dresden reunion (2011\u2013present)===\nOn December 31, 2010, Gabriel & Dresden reunited for special one off New Year's Eve celebration alongside [[ATB]] and Francis Preve at the [[Hollywood Palladium]] in Los Angeles.\n\nShortly afterward, the duo were booked on the [[Anjunabeats]] WMC Miami party at the Ice Palace as a special guest. Since this event, Gabriel & Dresden have officially announced themselves as reunited.\n\nSince the reunion, Gabriel & Dresden have performed at many clubs and festivals around the world including [[Electric Daisy Carnival]] (Las Vegas, Dallas, Chicago & Orlando), [[Tomorrowland (festival)|Tomorrowland]] in Belgium, [[Electric Zoo Festival]] in New York, [[Sunburn Festival]] in India, [[Beyond Wonderland|Escape From Wonderland]], [[Nocturnal Wonderland]], [[Paradiso Festival]], [[Creamfields Australia]], [[A State of Trance|ASOT 550: Invasion]], [[Ministry of Sound]], London, [[Zouk (club)|Zouk]] and a monthly residency at the [[Jason Strauss|Marquee Las Vegas]] in Las Vegas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bandsintown.com/GabrielAndDresden/past_events |title=Gabriel & Dresden Tour History from 2007 - 2014 - Gabriel & Dresden Past Tour Dates |publisher=Bandsintown.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011 they signed an artist deal with [[Armada Music]] which brought forth their mix compilation \"Mixed for Feet, Volume 1\" as well as numerous singles including 2012'a \"Play it Back\" featuring [[Betsie Larkin]], \"Tomorrow Comes\" with Neil Ormandy (2013), \"Shatter\" (with D-Wayne) and a re-working of [[Tracking Treasure Down|Tracking Treasure Down Revisited]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armadamusic.com/news/2011/12/we-welcome-gabriel-dresdens-organized-nature-label/ |title=\u00ab Armada Music |publisher=Armadamusic.com |date=2011-12-08 |accessdate=2014-08-01}}</ref>\n\nOn February 3, 2014, they restarted their monthly radio show \"Gabriel & Dresden present [[Organized Nature]]\" on [[Digitally Imported]]'s progressive channel. Since this show was already on the air in the past, it began this time around with Episode 30.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.di.fm/calendar/event/36131 |title=Organized Nature - with Gabriel & Dresden - DI Radio |publisher=Di.fm |accessdate=2014-08-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140618110918/http://www.di.fm/calendar/event/36131 |archivedate=2014-06-18 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGraduated in class of 88' from Westhill High School in Stamford, Connecticut.\n\nDresden got married in September 2012 to Holly Carrington. They have one daughter together, Charlotte Lily Dresden born on July 15, 2013. They filed for divorce in 2017 and the divorce was finalized in Austin, Texas on July 3, 2018.\n\n==Discography==\n''For discography as [[Gabriel & Dresden]], see [[Gabriel & Dresden#Discography|Gabriel & Dresden discography]].''<br />\n''For awards as [[Gabriel & Dresden]], see [[Gabriel & Dresden#Awards and nominations|Gabriel & Dresden Awards / Nominations]].''\n\n===Singles===\n*[[New Gold Dream]] (81-82-83-84) as The Consumers (with [[Dave Ralph]])\n*Use Only The Drugs (as Attention Deficit) 2003\n*Goddess <small>(as Summit)</small> 2004\n*[[Chris Cox (DJ)|Chris Cox]] & Dave Dresden - Whole Wide World 2008 (unreleased)\n*[[Morgan Page]] & Dave Dresden - I've Had Friends <small>(feat. [[Jan Burton]])</small> 2008 \n*Dave Dresden & Grayarea - Cloud Atlas 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] vs. Debo ft. Mezo - Keep Faith 2010 (released) Problem Child Rekords\n*Dave Dresden, [[Super 8 & Tab]] - Black Ice 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - That Day <small>(feat. [[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]])</small> 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - I Hear You Calling <small>(feat. David Penner & Essence)</small> 2009 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - Racecar (feat [[Holly Brook]]) 2010 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - Undertow (feat [[Holly Brook]]) 2010 (unreleased)\n*[[Dresden & Johnston]] - I Know You (Feat [[Holly Brook]]) 2010 (unreleased)\n\n===Remixes===\n*[[Lily Allen]] The Fear <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> 2009\n*[[Nadia Ali (singer)|Nadia Ali]] Love Story <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> 2009\n*[[BT (musician)|BT]] The Unbreakable <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> (unreleased)\n*[[JD Webb]] Better Man <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> 2009\n*[[The Crystal Method]] Black Rainbows <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small>\n*[[Enrique Iglesias]] feat. [[Ludacris]] Tonight <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small>\n*[[Morgan Page & Dave Dresden]] I've Had Friends <small> (as Dresden & Johnston)</small> (unreleased)\n*[[Linkin Park]] Waiting For The End <small> (as Dave Dresden) </small>\n\n===Compilations===\n* Trancendence - The First Wave 2000\n* Transit 200\n* Provocative Progressive 2002\n\n===Co-productions===\n* [[Armin van Buuren]] - Zocalo\n* [[Markus Schulz]] - Without You Near\n* [[Christina Aguilera]] - [[Hurt (Christina Aguilera song)]] <small>(Chris Cox Club Anthem)</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://myspace.co